I don’t use grocery delivery option very often because I’m so particular about how I shop for my groceries. Life has been life-ing lately so I got my groceries delivered. I needed to make a quick dinner so beef & broccoli it was! I ordered beef chuck steak. I wanted the small, flat cut, boneless ones, but the shopper picked this large, bone in steak. I made it work though! I simply cut them into bite sized pieces, chopped my veggies, and got busy. Dinner was ready in 30 minutes. The recipe is in my ebook “Dinner in 30” available for immediate download at shopthatnursecancook.com (link in bio)

How do you prefer your curry goat or chicken? With white rice or boiled food? Ever feel for something nice? Yep, me too. Curry goat with a few flour dumpling & green banana…and of course some white rice for these kids who don’t yet appreciate the goodness of boiled food! I’ve been toasting organic curry leaves with some curry: excellent flavor boost. I rinsed my banana with baking soda, water, & vinegar because I boil it in the same pot with the dumplings. (Cmon less dishes) Subscribe to my 🎥YouTube channel: thatnursecancook! Recipes are there! Google thatnursecancook and the dish you’re looking for if you can’t find it!
